article.headline: Maine 79, Brown 69
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP) -- Eric Dobson scored 19 points and four teammates also finished in double figures as Maine went on a strong run midway through the second half to defeat Brown 79-69 and win the Maine Invitational tournament Saturday. The Black Bears were leading 50-49 when they began the 21-5 run that was fueled by 13 second-half points from Kevin Reed, who finished with 18. Dobson added six rebounds and seven assists, while Freddy Petkus sank five of nine 3-pointers to finish with 15 points. Patrick Powers made seven 3-pointers and led all scorers with 23 points for Brown. Jaime Kilburn contributed 14. Maine held Brown to 36 percent shooting for the game, but committed 23 turnovers to only 12 for Brown. David Dubois, with 14 points, and Mark Flavin, with 10, were strong defensively inside for Maine, each grabbing nine rebounds. In the consolation game, Maine-Fort Kent defeated New England, 72-66.
